helpdesk-ticket.subject: Laptop Grad Image
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi there,
I stopped by IT yesterday to ask if I need to have the grad image applied to my laptop if I am enrolled for grad school beginning in the fall (MBA). My roommate is also starting grad school in the fall for perfusion, and he has the same question.
I have heard that we don’t need to do this if we are enrolled for the fall, but there wasn’t anyone at IT yesterday who could confirm. Is there any way you could let me know if I need to do this?
Thanks,
Zach Simpson
Zach Simpson Milwaukee School of Engineering B.S. Biomedical Engineering ‘18 (303) 916-9789 simpsonz@msoe.edu
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hi there,
 
I stopped by IT yesterday to ask if I need to have the grad image applied to my laptop if I am enrolled for grad school beginning in the fall (MBA). My roommate is also starting grad school in the fall for perfusion, and he has the same question.
 
I have heard that we don’t need to do this if we are enrolled for the fall, but there wasn’t anyone at IT yesterday who could confirm. Is there any way you could let me know if I need to do this?
 
Thanks,
 
Zach Simpson
 
Zach Simpson
Milwaukee School of Engineering
B.S. Biomedical Engineering ‘18
(303) 916-9789
simpsonz@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Zach Simpson, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30009 Thank you for contacting MSOE IT support! Anyone that is graduating with a bachelors degree must come through us to have a grad image applied to their laptop. If you're returning in the fall for say the AECM 5 year BS/MS degree program you don't come in for a new image quite yet (may be applicable to your roommate). In your case where you are coming back in the fall for your masters after receiving your bachelors, you must still come in for the reimage. For any required software that you need, graduates must rent a computer from us in order to utilize it. This is different for the Microsoft Office suite which you should still be able to access on https://office.microsoft.com/. Please let us know if you have any additional questions about this! Cheers, Austin Rovge 414.277.7288 Submit a Ticket: helpdesk@msoe.edu Monday – Thursday 7:30 AM – 7:00 PM Friday 7:30 AM – 5:00 PM Saturday and Sunday 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM "We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Zach Simpson,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30009

Thank you for contacting MSOE IT support!

Anyone that is graduating with a bachelors degree must come through us to have a grad image applied to their laptop. If you're returning in the fall for say the AECM 5 year BS/MS degree program you don't come in for a new image quite yet (may be applicable to your roommate).

In your case where you are coming back in the fall for your masters after receiving your bachelors, you must still come in for the reimage. For any required software that you need, graduates must rent a computer from us in order to utilize it. This is different for the Microsoft Office suite which you should still be able to access on https://office.microsoft.com/.

Please let us know if you have any additional questions about this!

Cheers,
Austin Rovge

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Luke Ponga, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30026 I think we found the answer for you guys! In Outlook, click on the gear (Settings) in the upper right-hand corner and choose 'Mail' under 'Your app settings.' Next, go to Layout>Message Format and check the box for 'Always show From' and Save when done. When you go to send an email, you should now have the option to send from the SAME account. Please let us know if this works for you and your group! Respectfully, Amanda Goff 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Helpdesk Summer Hours: Monday-Friday 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Saturday-Sunday CLOSED "We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Luke Ponga,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30026
I think we found the answer for you guys! In Outlook, click on the gear (Settings) in the upper right-hand corner and choose 'Mail' under 'Your app settings.'
Next, go to Layout>Message Format and check the box for 'Always show From' and Save when done. 
When you go to send an email, you should now have the option to send from the SAME account. Please let us know if this works for you and your group!

Respectfully,
Amanda Goff

helpdesk-note.body: Hi David Gonzalez-Salzwedel, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30067 What is the specific update that it is trying to run? Also, are there any updates in Software Center? If so, you might want to try running those updates first. Kaspersky Endpoint Security should update automatically and not cause issues with Windows updates. However, on the lower right hand corner, in the Windows task bar, there is an upward arrow. If you click on that, you can then click on the Kaspersky icon (a red V with an arrow) to open the panel. Under the Protection and Control tab you can select Tasks, and run "Update" by right-clicking on it to confirm that the application is up to date. Kaspersky cannot be disabled or uninstalled. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark, Before my unexpected absence I was able to pull SAT & ACT scores. But not the way I would like. In Jenzabar the test scores show up as a whole number like 25 but in the database it display like 25.0000. I can get the script to sync test scores as a whole number but if someone doesn't have a test score it will sync 0 for the score. When I try to get the script to sync not to sync 0 for candidates who don't have a score, the candidates who do have a test score sync exactly how it displays in the database (25.0000) Which approach do you prefer I take? Thanks Mike Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30074 Hi Mike, I have added the following fields to undergraduate spectrum: ACT Composite ACT Math ACT Reading ACT Science ACT English SAT Composite SAT Critical Reading SAT Math
Could you please set up the sync from Spectrum to Jenzabar (processing of apps) to carry this information through and then have the nightly file going back from JZ to spectrum carry the information back and always update what is in spectrum if there is something in JZ?
Thanks!
Mark Anderson Milwaukee School of Engineering +1 (414) 277-4544
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mark,

Before my unexpected absence I was able to pull SAT & ACT scores.  But not the way I would like.  In Jenzabar the test scores show up as a whole number like 25 but in the database it display like 25.0000.



I can get the script to sync test scores as a whole number but if someone doesn't have a test score it will sync 0 for the score.   

When I try to get the script to sync not to sync 0 for candidates who don't have a score, the candidates who do have a test score sync exactly how it displays in the database (25.0000)

Which approach do you prefer I take?

Thanks
Mike

helpdesk-ticket.description:

Since the class has no textbook - wanted to place all materials on "box" as they would be preserved there and the students could download the info if they desire to. Need help doing that - best to simply come into the help desk? 2. I have an MSOE computer - hope to teach again but it appears that will not happen until the winter quarter later this year. Do I return the computer or keep it?
Thanks a lot,
Bill

helpdesk-note.body: Hi William Krill, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30183 Thank you for contacting MSOE IT support! I'm sorry about the delay in responding, we've been extremely busy with the senior graduates and the faculty swaps. In order to get material posted on blackboard to box, you'll have to upload the content separately to box and change the share settings on the documents to be open the public. From there you can share the URL with your students. As for the MSOE computer, if your contract is up with MSOE and it is not getting renewed then you must return the laptop. Since you said you teach again in winter quarter I am assuming your contract is still active. Can you confirm this? Please let us know if you have any additional questions! helpdesk-note.body: Hi Joshua Hummel, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/30184 The helpdesk closes at 4:30 pm, and we are open Monday through Friday (see our hours below). If you can drop the laptop off by around 4 today we could start the process and it would be ready Monday morning. After that time, the image would likely not get started, and would be ready for you later on the day on Monday. The imaging process is quoted at 2 hours, but sometimes takes less time, as previously mentioned. If you are unable to come in today, please feel free to stop by on Monday. If this is not possible, you may authorize someone else to drop off the laptop for you; we just need to know their name and a rough time they might stop by. Please let us know what your plans are! Good Morning,
We have a student that just graduated, but needs to finish some Senior Design work using Solidworks. He is anticipating about two weeks to complete the work. Would he be able to use Solidworks on his laptop? Or perhaps, he could have login credentials to use the Harley Lab computers?

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Web Updates
helpdesk-ticket.description:
https://www.msoe.edu/grohmann-museum/the-collection/
The Eckhart G. Grohmann Museum Collection “Man at Work” is comprised of more than 1,300 paintings and sculptures from 1580 to the present. They reflect a variety of artistic styles and subjects that document the evolution of organized work—from farming and mining to trades as glassblowing and seaweed gathering. Later, it is machines and men embodying the paradoxes of industrialism: dark factory interiors with glowing molten metal juxtaposed with workers.
Also, this area needs to be updated to over 1300:
[cid:image001.png@01D3F73F.97F8ED70] JAMES R. KIESELBURG, II Director

https://www.msoe.edu/grohmann-museum/the-collection/
 
The Eckhart G. Grohmann Museum Collection “Man at Work”  is comprised of more than 1,300 paintings and sculptures from 1580 to the present. They reflect a variety of artistic styles and subjects that document the evolution of organized work—from farming and mining to trades as glassblowing and seaweed gathering. Later, it is machines and men embodying the paradoxes of industrialism: dark factory interiors with glowing molten metal juxtaposed with workers.
 
Also, this area needs to be updated to over 1300:
 
JAMES R. KIESELBURG, II
Director
 
Grohmann Museum
Milwaukee  School  of  Engineering
t:414.277.7139         f:414.277.2837
